# Overlays and mobile-first layout

## Default pattern for long forms in modals

- **Fixed chrome**: title row + optional description stay in a **non-scrolling** header.
- **Single scroll root**: one inner region (`flex-1 min-h-0 overflow-y-auto`) holds the form fields.
- **Fixed footer**: primary actions (submit) in a **non-scrolling** footer with top border.
- **Safe areas**: use `env(safe-area-inset-*)` on the modal panel edges where content meets notches/home indicators.
- **Viewport height**: prefer `max-h-[min(90vh,100dvh)]` on the panel so iOS dynamic viewport behaves predictably.

Prefer **Headless UI `Dialog`** for new full-screen-style overlays that match this pattern (see `CreateBudgetLineDialog`, `EditBudgetLinePricingSheet`, `CreateItemYieldDialog`, `CreateProjectDialog`).

## Headless UI `Dialog` and sheet-like panels

- Treat panel content as **`flex flex-col max-h-[100dvh] min-h-0 overflow-hidden`** (or `max-h-[min(90vh,100dvh)]` per above) and put **one** scrollable child inside — avoid `overflow-y-auto` on the whole panel plus nested portaled overlays that fight clipping.

## Select (`Listbox`) and portaling

- Headless **Listbox** options render in a portal by default. Only override portal/`anchor` behavior when body portaling breaks inside a clipped ancestor — document why in a short comment. Do not thread refs from parent dialogs “just in case”.

## `PopoverContent` (custom)

- Optional `container` prop is supported for rare cases (popover inside clipped scroll). Default remains body portal.

## Before merging overlay work

Run `npm run full-check --prefix fe` and manually smoke on **iOS Safari** and **Android Chrome**:

- Open / close / backdrop tap; dismiss works as expected
- Scroll **inside** the modal only (background should not scroll)
- With **on-screen keyboard** open, primary actions (e.g. submit) stay reachable
- Open any **select** or suggestion list: taps register, no clipping

User-visible copy stays **Spanish (es-AR)**; file and symbol names stay **English** (see project rules).
